FBIS4-15362 "drsov068_t_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Russian Military Exercise Causes `Alarm' Russian Military Exercise Causes `Alarm' WS0804101994 Tallinn ETA in English 0728 GMT 8 Apr 94 WS0804101994 Tallinn ETA English BFN [From 8 April PAEVALEHT, p 3; "News Bulletin" No. 67] [Text] The Russian military held an exercise at the shooting range in Manniku, causing some alarm among the public. The Defence Forces GHQ and the police had not been informed of the training. Defence Ministry press secretary Maige Priim explained that the explosions had been caused by hand grenades, adding that the Russians had not asked for the permission of the Estonian authorities to hold the exercise.
